description: QuickSE lets rooted Android users view and change SELinux mode easily. QuickSE is a lightweight and open-source Android utility for rooted devices that helps you manage SELinux mode with ease. Core Features: * Instantly view the current SELinux status. * Toggle SELinux mode between Enforcing and Permissive. * Enable Auto-toggle on boot to apply your preferred SELinux mode automatically after restarting. * Schedule automatic SELinux mode changes at a specific time. * Get notified whenever SELinux mode changes occur. Kernel Inspector: Access low-level device info from /proc and other system files: * Kernel information * Loaded kernel modules * Kernel symbols * Kernel configuration * System uptime * System load average * CPU information * Memory information * Kernel logs Built entirely with Jetpack Compose and Material3. Contributions, forks, and feedback are welcome.
